de.oaam.model.oaam.library

Interface DeviceType

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier, OaamBaseElementA, ResourceConsumerA, ResourceProviderA
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DeviceTypeImpl

    public interface DeviceType
extends ResourceConsumerA, ResourceProviderA, OaamBaseElementA
    A representation of the model object 'Device Type'. A definition of a device type. This holds the properties and resources that are identical for each device of this type

    The following features are supported:

    • Io Declarations
    • Is Subdevice
    • Can Have Subdevices
    • Mtbf
    • Weight
    • Cost
    • Io Groups
    • Is Self Managing
    See Also:
    LibraryPackage.getDeviceType()

      • isIsSubdevice

        boolean isIsSubdevice()
        Returns the value of the 'Is Subdevice' attribute. The default value is "false". Defines if this device type can be used as a subdevice in any other device. A subdevice is e.g. a blade in a cabinet.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Is Subdevice' attribute.
        See Also:
